The South African Weather Service has issued a warning of thunderstorm and heavy rains in parts of KwaZulu-Natal. Forecaster Wiseman Dlamini says the northern part of the province will be mostly affected, but there will be rain in other parts too “It’s gonna be 30 percent showers and thunderstorm over southern part. However, its gonna be fifty to eighty percent for central and northern part of KZN from this afternoon. The conditions are expected to improve tomorrow especially in the southern part of KZN where showers are expected maybe half of the day in the afternoon, it’s gonna be in the north coast – fifty percent of thundershowers expected. Today we have a warning – there is severe thunderstorm expected in some part of Zululand district areas including Phongola, Vryheid and etc.”